message.content:
1. The cLDA model was applied to all available data.
2. The total number of data points available was 233.
3. The application of the cLDA model resulted in an LDL improvement.
4. The LDL improvement was 8.9 mg/dL.
5. The 95% confidence interval for the LDL improvement was between -16.7 to -1.0.
6. The p-value for the LDL improvement was 0.03.
7. The LDL improvement was in comparison to usual care.
8. The comparison was made for GMC.

messages.content:
Statement: With all available data (n=233), applying the cLDA model yielded an LDL improvement of 8.9 mg/dL (95% CI −16.7 to −1.0; p=0.03) for GMC compared with usual care.
